value.value: A sclerenchyma cell (PO:0000077) that is elongated and tapering.

definition.value: May or may not have lignin in the secondary cell wall (GO:0009531) or a living protoplast at maturity. It may be difficult to distinguish fiber cells from tracheary elements (PO:0000290). Compare with sclerid cells (PO:0025418), which are usually not elongated.

value.value: A portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015) that develops from a procambium (PO:0025275).

definition.value: Forms as part of primary growth (GO term for primary growth has been requested).

value.value: A portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015) that develops from a vascular cambium (PO:0005598).

definition.value: Forms as part of secondary growth (GO:0080117) in vascular plants. Often differentiated into the axial system (PO:0025410) and ray system (PO:0025411).

value.value: A portion of secondary vascular tissue (PO:0025409) that has as parts cells derived from fusiform initials (PO:0000079) and oriented with their longest diameter parallel to a plant axis (PO:0025004).

definition.value: Includes portions of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) and axial wood parenchyma (PO:0004533).

value.value: A portion of secondary vascular tissue (PO:0025409) that has as part ray wood parenchyma (PO:0004534) and extends radially in the secondary xylem (PO:0005848) and secondary phloem (PO:0005848) of a plant axis (PO:0025004).

definition.value: May include ray tracheids, as in Pinaceae and some Cupressaceae.

value.value: A parenchyma cell (PO:0000074) that is morphologically and physiologically associated with a sieve cell (PO:0025415) but does is not derived from the same initial cell (PO:0004011) as the sieve cell.

definition.value: May be found in the ray system (PO:0025411) and sometimes the axial system (PO:0025410) of gymnosperms. Compare to companion cells (PO:0000071), which are found in angiosperms.

value.value: A leaf lamina vein (PO:0020138) that connects directly to a petiole vascular system (PO:0000052) or a shoot axis vascular system (PO:0000039).

definition.value: Generally the largest and most prominent of the leaf veins. A leaf may have more than one primary vein. The central primary vein is the midvein (PO:0020139). Vein orders only apply to hierarchically branching vein patterns, not to dichotomously branching vein patterns, as found in some ferns and gymnosperms.

value.value: A lateral meristem (PO:0020145) that is not contiguous with an apical meristem (PO:0020144) and has a parts multiple layers of meristematic cells (PO:0004010).

definition.value: Contributes mainly to formation of the body of a stem (PO:0009047), but may also produce adventitious (shoot-borne) roots (PO:0000042) and may also be found in the roots (PO:0009005) of some species. May be continuous or discontinuous with the primary thickening meristem (PO:0005039). Found in some monocot species of the Liliales and Asperigales.

value.value: A sieve element (PO:0025406) in which the sieve areas are not aggregated into sieve plates (GO:0097218).

definition.value: Sieve areas in sieve cells generally have narrow pores and thin connecting strands, and they are not highly specialized, but instead are fairly uniform throughout the cell wall. Typical of gymnosperms and non-seed vascular plants such as ferns. Differ from sieve tube elements, which have sieve plates and more pronounced specialization of sieve areas.

value.value: A portion of phloem tissue (PO:0005417) that has as parts a series of sieve tube elements (PO:0000289) arranged end to end and interconnected through sieve plates.

definition.value: A sieve plate is part of a sieve tube member.

value.value: A portion of xylem (PO:0005352) tissue that has as parts a tube-like series of vessel members (PO:0002003), the common walls of which have perforations.
A sclerenchyma cell (PO:0000077) with many pits in the secondary cell wall.

definition.value: Usually not very elongated. The lumen of a sclerid cell is occluded by the secondary cell wall.

value.value: A fiber tracheid (PO:0000355) that has as parts one or more thin internal partitions or septa.

definition.value: A septate fiber tracheid septum is composed of the adjacent primary cell walls of two internal cells that arise from mitosis within the septate fiber tracheid after it has formed a secondary cell wall (GO:0009531).

value.value: A libriform fiber cell (PO:0004520) that has as parts one or more thin internal partitions or septa.

definition.value: A septate libriform fiber cell septum is composed of the adjacent primary cell walls of two internal cells that arise from mitosis within the septate libriform fiber cell after it has formed a secondary cell wall (GO:0009531).

value.value: A phloem fiber cell (PO:0004519) that has as parts one or more thin internal partitions or septa.

definition.value: A septatephloem fiber cell septum is composed of the adjacent primary cell walls of two internal cells that arise from mitosis within the septate phloem fiber cell after it has formed a secondary cell wall (GO:0009531).

value.value: A xylem fiber cell (PO:0000274) in which the inner-most layer of the secondary cell wall (GO:0009531) contains abundant cellulose and is poor in lignin.

definition.value: Often found in reaction wood in dicots and in some phloem fiber cells (PO:0004519), as in Linum usitatissimum. In gelatinous fiber cells, the inner layer of the cell wall is a cellulosic gelatinous-layer or G-layer, which may be relatively porous and less compact than the outer layers of the cell wall and may absorb water and swell.

value.value: A plant structure development stage (PO:0009012) that has as primary participant a portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007).
A plant tissue development stage (PO:0025423) that has as primary participant a portion of vascular tissue (PO:0009015).
A vascular tissue development stage (PO:0025424) that has as primary participant a portion of xylem (PO:0005352) tissue.
A vascular tissue development stage (PO:0025424) that has as primary participant a portion of phloem (PO:0005417) tissue.

A xylem development stage (PO:0025425) that has as primary participant a portion of secondary xylem (PO:0005848) tissue during the interval between the beginning of a cell division stage of secondary xylem (PO:0025463) and the death of the last living cell in the secondary xylem.

definition.value: During a secondary xylem development stage (also called a wood development stage), the cells of secondary xylem (PO:0005848), including tracheary elements (PO:0000290), xylem fiber cells (PO:0000274), and wood parenchyma cells (PO:0004525) undergo cellular developmental processes (GO:0048869) such as cell division (GO:0051301), cell growth (GO:0016049), cell differentiation (GO:0030154), or cell death (GO:0008219). The transition from sapwood to heartwood marks the end of the secondary xylem development stage.

value.value: A portion of meristem (PO:0009013) tissue in which the planes of cell division in each layer are anticlinal to the surface of the phyllome (PO:0006001).

definition.value: The activity of a phyllome plate meristem results in increase in the surface area, but not thickness of a phyllome.

value.value: A phyllome plate meristem (PO:0025428) in the vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

definition.value: The activity of a leaf plate meristem results in increase in the surface area, but not thickness of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025).

value.value: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and will give rise to a phyllome primordium (PO:0025128).

definition.value: The phyllome anlagen is only detectable by gene expression, not morphology.

value.value: A phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) that will give rise to a vascular leaf primordium (PO:0000017) and is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).

definition.value: This is the region where you have the maximum concentration of auxin in the SAM (at least in a few species that have been studied).

value.value: A phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) that will give rise to a cotyledon primordium (PO:0000015) and is part of a peripheral zone (PO:000225) of an embryo shoot apical meristem (PO:0006362).
A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is committed to the development of a root primordium (PO:0005029).

definition.value: Only detectable by gene expression, not morphology. May arise in a pericycle (PO:0006203), as for lateral roots in most seed plants, an endodermis (PO:0000252), as for lateral roots in ferns, or from parenchyma cells (PO:0000074) that are part a shoot axis (PO:0025029), in the case of a basal root (PO:0025002) or shoot-borne root (PO:0000042).

value.value: A vascular bundle (PO:0005020) that is part of a petiole vascular system (PO:0000052).
A cork cambium (PO:0005599) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).
A cork cambium (PO:0005599) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).
A vascular cambium (PO:0005598) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).
A vascular cambium (PO:0005598) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is part of a plant axis (PO:0025004) and has as parts a cambium (PO:0005597) and adjacent cells.

definition.value: The cambial zone generally consists of the initial cells of the cambium and their immediate derivatives, arranged in radial files. This term is used for the cambium (PO:0005597) and surrounding area, especially when the borders of the cambium are not clear.

value.value: A cambial zone that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029).

definition.value: Includes a cambium (PO:0005597) and adjacent cells. This term is used when the borders of the cambium are not clear.

value.value: A cambial zone that is part of a root (PO:0009005).

definition.value: Includes a cambium (PO:0005597) and adjacent cells. This term is used when the borders of the cambium are not clear.

value.value: A secondary thickening meristem (PO:0025414) that is part of a stem (PO:0009047).
A secondary thickening meristem (PO:0025414) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).
A tracheary element (PO:0000290) that is part of a primary xylem tissue (PO:0005849).
A tracheary element (PO:0000290) that is part of a portion of secondary xylem tissue (PO:0005848).
A tracheid (PO:0000301) that is part of a xylem tissue (PO:0005849).
A tracheid PO:0000301 that is part of a portion of secondary xylem tissue (PO:0005848).
A xylem vessel member (PO:0002003) that is part of a primary xylem tissue (PO:0005849).
A xylem vessel member (PO:0002003) that is part of a portion of secondary xylem tissue (PO:0005848).
A xylem vessel (PO:0025417) that is part of a primary xylem tissue (PO:0005849).
A xylem vessel (PO:0025417) that is part of a portion of secondary xylem tissue (PO:0005848).
A sieve element (PO:0025406) that is part of a portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075).
A sieve element (PO:0025406) that is part of a portion of secondary phloem (PO:0005043).
A sieve cell (PO:0025415) that is part of a portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075).
A sieve tube element (PO:0000289) that is part of a portion of primary phloem (PO:0006075).
A sieve cell (PO:0025415) that is part of a portion of secondary phloem (PO:0005043).
